<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,1381]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1320,1345]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from the Greek, 
<emphasis box="[879,970,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">drepane</emphasis>
(= sickle), referring to the sickle-shaped caudal processes of the juxta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
